<body>
    <h1>Updating eZ Platform</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>This page explains how to update eZ Platform to a new version.</p>
<p>In the instructions below, replace<code> &lt;version&gt;</code> with the=
 version of eZ Platform you are updating to (for example: <code>v1.7.0</cod=
e>). If you are testing a release candidate, use the<a href=3D"https://gith=
ub.com/ezsystems/ezplatform/releases" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow"> latest rc tag</a> (for example: <code>v1.7.1-rc1</code>).</p>
<h1 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-Version-specificsteps">Version-specific steps<=
/h1>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>Some versions introduce new features that require taking special=
 steps; they are marked on this page with yellow tags.</strong></p>
<p>If you intend to skip a version (for example, update directly from v1.3 =
to v1.5 without getting v1.4), remember to look at all the intermediate ste=
ps as well =E2=80=93 this means you need to perform both the steps for v1.4=
 and v1.5.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-Updateprocedure">Update procedure</h1>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-1.Checkoutaversion">1. Check out a version</h2=
>
<p><strong>1.1.</strong> From the project's root, create a new branch from =
the project's master, or from the branch you're updating on:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your master branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git checkout -b &lt;branch_name&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>This creates a new project branch for the update based on your current p=
roject branch, typically <code>master</code>. An example <code>&lt;branch_n=
ame&gt;</code> would be <code>update-1.4</code>.</p>
<p><strong>1.2.</strong> If it's not there, add <code>ezsystems/ezplatform<=
/code> (or&nbsp;<code>ezsystems/ezstudio</code>, when updating an Enterpris=
e installation) as an upstream remote:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your new update branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git remote add ezplatform http://github.com/ezsystems/ezplatform.g=
it
or
git remote add ezstudio http://github.com/ezsystems/ezstudio.git</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>1.3.</strong> Then pull the tag into your branch.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If you are unsure which version to pull, run <code>git ls-remote --tags<=
/code> to list all possible tags.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your new update branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git pull ezplatform &lt;version&gt;
or
git pull ezstudio &lt;version&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>At this stage you may get conflicts, which are a normal part of the proc=
edure and no reason to worry. The most common ones will be on <code>compose=
r.json</code>&nbsp;and <code>composer.lock</code>.</p>
<p>The latter can be ignored, as it will be regenerated when we execute <co=
de>composer update</code> later. The easiest is to checkout the version fro=
m the tag and add it to the changes:</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If you get a <strong>lot</strong> of conflicts (on the&nbsp;<code>doc</c=
ode>&nbsp;folder for instance), and eZ Platform was installed from the <a h=
ref=3D"http://share.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">share.e=
z.no</a> tarball, it might be because of incomplete history. You will have =
to run&nbsp;<code>git fetch ezplatform --unshallow</code> (or <code>git fet=
ch ezstudio --unshallow</code>) to load the full history, and run the merge=
 again.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your new update branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git checkout --theirs composer.lock &amp;&amp; git add composer.lo=
ck</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>If you do not keep a copy in the branch, you may also run:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your new update branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git rm composer.lock</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-2.Mergecomposer.json">2. Merge composer.json</=
h2>
<h4 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-Manualmerging">Manual merging</h4>
<p>Conflicts in <code>composer.json</code>&nbsp;need to be fixed manually. =
If you're not familiar with the diff output, you may checkout the tag's ver=
sion and inspect the changes. It should be readable for most:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>From your new update branch</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">git checkout --theirs composer.json &amp;&amp; git diff HEAD compo=
ser.json</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>You should see what was changed, as compared to your own version, in the=
 diff output. The update changes the requirements for all of the&nbsp;<code=
>ezsystems/</code> packages. Those changes should be left untouched. All of=
 the other changes will be removals of what you added for your own project.=
 Use <code>git checkout -p</code>&nbsp;to selectively cancel those changes:=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">git checkout -p composer.json</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Answer&nbsp;<code>no</code>&nbsp;(do not discard) to the requirement cha=
nges of&nbsp;<code>ezsystems</code> dependencies. Answer <code>yes</code>&n=
bsp;(discard) to removals of your changes.</p>
<p>Once you are done, inspect the file, either using an editor or by runnin=
g <code>git diff composer.json</code>. You may also test the file's sanity =
with <code>composer validate</code>, and&nbsp;test the dependencies by runn=
ing&nbsp;<code>composer update --dry-run</code>. (will output what it would=
 do to dependencies, without applying the changes.</p>
<p>Once finished, run&nbsp;<code>git add composer.json</code> and commit<co=
de>.</code></p>
<h4 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-Fixingotherconflicts(ifany)">Fixing other conf=
licts (if any)</h4>
<p>Depending on the local changes you have done, you may get other conflict=
s on configuration files, kernel, etc.</p>
<p>There shouldn't be many, and you should be able to figure out which valu=
e is the right one for all of them:</p>
<ul>
<li>Edit the file, and identify the conflicting changes.&nbsp;If a setting =
you have modified has also been changed by us, you should be able to figure=
 out which value is the right one.</li>
<li>Run&nbsp;<code>git add conflicting-file</code>&nbsp;to add the changes<=
/li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-3.Updatetheapp">3. Update the app</h2>
<p>At this point, you should have a <code>composer.json</code> file with th=
e correct requirements. Run&nbsp;<code>composer update</code> to update the=
 dependencies.&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">composer update</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If you want to first test how the update proceeds without actually updat=
ing any packages, you can try the command with the&nbsp;<code>--dry-run</co=
de> switch:</p>
<p><code>composer update --dry-run</code></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title">On PHP conflict | 16.02 and later requires PHP 5.5 or hi=
gher</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Because from release 16.02 onwards eZ Platform is compatible only with P=
HP 5.5 and higher, the update command above will fail if you use an older P=
HP version. Please update PHP to proceed.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-4.Updatedatabase">4. Update database</h2>
<p>This step is only relevant for some releases:</p>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: #ffffff;border-width: 1px;"=
>
<div class=3D"panelHeader" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px;background-col=
or: #ffffff;">
<b>Form Builder</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: #ffffff;">=20
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">1.7.0</span=
></p>
<p>To enable the Form Builder feature in eZ Platform Enterprise Edition, im=
port the following file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">mysql -p -u &lt;database_user&gt; &lt;database_name&gt; &lt; vendor=
/ezsystems/ezstudio-form-builder/bundle/Resources/install/form_builder.sql<=
/pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: #ffffff;border-width: 1px;"=
>
<div class=3D"panelHeader" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px;background-col=
or: #ffffff;">
<b>Date Based Publisher</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: #ffffff;">=20
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">1.7.0</span=
></p>
<p>To enable the Date-Based Publisher feature in Enterprise, import the fol=
lowing file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">mysql -p -u &lt;database_user&gt; &lt;database_name&gt; &lt; vendor=
/ezsystems/date-based-publisher/bundle/Resources/install/datebasedpublisher=
_scheduled_version.sql</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>In order to activate Date-Based Publisher open console (terminal) and us=
e:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">crontab -e</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>and add below configuration at the end of edited file.</p>
<p>For production environment:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">* * * * *   (cd /path/to/your/ezstudio-project &amp;&amp; app/conso=
le ezpublish:cron:run -e=3Dprod)</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>For development environment:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">* * * * *   (cd /path/to/your/ezstudio-project &amp;&amp; app/conso=
le ezpublish:cron:run -e=3Ddev)</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-5.Dumpassets">5. Dump assets</h2>
<p>The web assets must be dumped again if you are using the <code>prod</cod=
e> environment. In <code>dev</code> this happens automatically:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php app/console assetic:dump -e=3Dprod</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>If you encounter problems, additionally clear the cache and install asse=
ts:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php app/console cache:clear -e=3Dprod
php app/console assets:install --symlink -e=3Dprod
php app/console assetic:dump -e=3Dprod</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"UpdatingeZPlatform-6.Commit,testandmerge">6. Commit, test and mer=
ge</h2>
<p>Once all the conflicts have been resolved, and <code>composer.lock</code=
>&nbsp;updated, the merge can be committed. Note that you may or may not ke=
ep&nbsp;<code>composer.lock</code>, depending on your version management wo=
rkflow. If you do not wish to keep it, run&nbsp;<code>git reset HEAD &lt;fi=
le&gt;</code> to remove it from the changes.&nbsp;Run&nbsp;<code>git commit=
</code>, and adapt the message if necessary. You can now verify the project=
 and once the update has been approved, go back to <code>master</code>, and=
 merge your update branch:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">git checkout master
git merge &lt;branch_name&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Your eZ Platform should now be up-to-date with the chosen versio=
n!</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
